G.Damn. &quot;Mr.&quot; DocDel, you are the most frustrating guy to communicate with, lately, that I know. I thing Gerald hit it right between both our eyes, when he said that we are too &quot;busy screaming past each other&quot; to talk.<br><br>
You have been flaming at me for two or three days straight, and accusing me of &quot;tactics&quot; that you yourself employee and others that I don't agree with, or totally don't know where yu are coming from.  <br><br>
Allow me an opportunity to set the record straight, as I see it.  We agree on far more things than we disagree on.  The biggest disagreement is on multi-culturalism versus assimilation. You made an assumption that assimilation means captulation. No. I never said nor thought that.  I see all the cultural groups in America as ok. None better, none worse. But (and here is where we lost each other), I want my America to be a land of American Culture, which is taken from all the sub-cultures (like where would we be with out salsa, bagels, hot dogs, scotch, etc), speaking English, and conducting the business of government, and education, in English.  What anyone does at home is their own business.  I do not want to see election ballots being printed in 12 or 24 different languages. It was in 4 at the last election and that really pisses me off.  To me, becoming a citizen of the USA means you should learn the language. And most of the customs of America.  It does not mean you must &quot;lose&quot; your previous culture or customs.  That is not capitulation, that is merger.  I am not an German-Russian-Polish-Jewish-White-Whatever-American. I don't like all those prefixes, and I think in the long run they well fragment our society, instead of enriching it.  <br><br>
You apparently disagree with that. (what an understatement). Gerald is also right about Little Saigon only being around for 20 or so years.  As I think about that, Jesus, How can I non think about it, you keep slapping me in the face with it, the issue I have is not with Vietnamese, it is with any immigrant group that comes to America, takes from America, and does not offer anything to enrich the American &quot;pot&quot;.  It is my value that someday, all of America, and maybe the whole world, will end up speaking one language and having one skin color, even purple.  Then we might move beyond other stupid concepts like nationalism, group think, boundaries, class warfare, class hatred (God, look at what is happening in Africa, just over tribal allegience, they both have the same skin colors and languge, and genocide is the rule of the day in Zaire and Rewanda).   <br><br>
The old Science Fiction books I read as a kid always showed the Earth coming together as one people in defense of the mother planet when it was attacked by Martians, or &quot;them&quot; in the spaceships. Strangly, that is my ideal.  I think it is a better alternative than complete fragmentation and the probable nuclear WW3 that blows us all up.<br><br>
You comment about how I treat people is perplexing. Clearly I do not see how I treat people as you do.  I thought I may be too blunt at times, too honest, too opinionated, but never purposely attacking. We all know that what we think we do is usually not what others see.  Ditto for you too.  <br><br>
Almost Lastly, &quot;Mr.&quot; Doc Del, and I am calling you Mister as a joke, in case you don't understand my humor, now that I am <br>
just &quot;spatz' to you, because I don't get your issue over your name.  I called you by your first name out of frustration, and comradrie, not out of any mind game.  A name is a name is a name, and I had no idea that you have &quot;secret&quot; or different value-levels (&quot;it is a biggie to me&quot;) to which name you go by.  Somehow, using your first name seemed, at the time, to fit the frustration I was drowning in, and I didn't give it a second thought. As for my intimidating, disgusting, changing the subject, and other horrible acts that you say I continue to do, Huh?  Why are you so upset with me?  You really have lost me, perhaps this post will help focus you, and thus, me.  I had no idea that I was &quot;dissing&quot; you by using your name, and so my apology is tended.<br><br>
Lastly, where this entire thread started: Lien.  Her first post, and you can go back and re-read it if you forgot it, came in with an attitude directed at me.  Remember?  I challenged her pre-conceived (as I thought it was) attitude about me, and got no where.  I did not &quot;destroy&quot; her or chase her away.  I think she is still out there laughing her bright head off at the two old farts who are screaming past each other, and how she openned up a can of worms for those old geezers.   (and Gerald, thanks for being our moderator).<br><br>
